attributes.info:
{"description":"SDG 15.3 aims to combat desertification, restore degraded land and soil, including land affected by desertification, drought and floods, and strive to achieve a land degradation-neutral world by 2030. The i) land cover, ii) land productivity and iii) carbon stocks are combined to measure the proportion of land that is degraded over total land area. This data layer is a preliminary assessment and evaluation of changes in land cover and soil carbon combined with an analysis of land productivity status and trends based on net primary productivity.",
"source":"<p>UNCCD 2017. Good Practice Guidance. SDG Indicator 15.3.1. Proportion of land that is degraded over total land area. Version 1.0 Available from: https://www.unccd.int/sites/default/files/relevant-links/2021-03/Indicator_15.3.1_GPG_v2_29Mar_Advanced-version.pdf</p><p>Trends.Earth. Conservation International. Available online at: http://trends.earth. 2018.</p>",
"link":"http://trends.earth"}

{"description":"Land cover refers to the observed physical cover of the Earth’s surface which describes the distribution of vegetation types, water bodies and human-made infrastructure. It also reflects the use of land resources, i.e. soil, water and biodiversity, for agriculture, forestry, human settlements and other purposes. For SDG indicator 15.3.1 land cover is defined by i. changes in land cover that may point to land degradation when there is a loss in productivity in terms of ecosystem services considered desirable in local or national context; ii. a land cover classification system that can be used to disaggregate the other two sub-indicators, thus increasing the indicator’s policy relevance. The land cover degradation output was derived using European Space Agency’s Climate Change Initiative on Land Cover (ESA-CCI-LC) 300m resolution products to compare changes from a baseline period (2000-2014) to a target year (2015). A transition matrix designates each land cover transition as improved, stable or degraded to create the final output.", 
"source":"<p>UNCCD 2017. Good Practice Guidance. SDG Indicator 15.3.1. Proportion of land that is degraded over total land area. Version 1.0 Available from: http://www2.unccd.int/sites/default/files/relevant-links/2017-10/Good%20Practice%20Guidance_ SDG%20Indicator%2015.3.1_Version%201.0.pdf</p><p>Trends.Earth. Conservation International. Available online at: http://trends.earth. 2018.</p>",
"link":"http://trends.earth"}

{"description":"Soil Organic Carbon (SOC) is the third sub-indicator used to measure degradation. Changes in vegetation cover, including those in response to climate or land use or management, influence SOC stocks by altering the rates, quality, and location of plant litter inputs to soils.Therefore, change in land cover are used to estimate changes in carbon stock for mineral soils and default annual emission factors to estimate the losses of carbon following drainage and/or fire for organic soils. Land cover in 2015 is compared to the baseline period to measure vegetative loss by category and estimate changes in carbon stock.",
"source":"<p>Hengl, T., Mendes de Jesus, J., Heuvelink, G. B.M., Ruiperez Gonzalez, M., Kilibarda, M. et al., 2017. SoilGrids250m: global gridded soil information based on Machine Learning. PLOS One. Available from: http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0169748</p><p>ESA Land Cover CCI project team; Defourny, P. (2016): ESA Land Cover Climate Change Initiative (Land_Cover_cci): MERIS Surface Reflectance. Centre for Environmental Data Analysis, 12/15/2017. Available from: http://catalogue.ceda.ac.uk/uuid/e80f28ccb0504c32b403eee654a8a5b3</p><p>UNCCD 2017. Good Practice Guidance. SDG Indicator 15.3.1. Proportion of land that is degraded over total land area. Version 1.0 Available from: http://www2.unccd.int/sites/default/files/relevant-links/2017-10/Good%20Practice%20Guidance_ SDG%20Indicator%2015.3.1_Version%201.0.pdf</p><p>Trends.Earth. Conservation International. Available online at: http://trends.earth. 2018.</p>",
"link":"http://trends.earth"}

{"description":"Soil Organic Carbon (SOC) is used as a proxy to measure carbon stocks responsible for assessing degradation resulting from changes in carbon stocks. Changes in vegetation cover, including those in response to climate or land use or management, influence SOC stocks by altering the rates, quality, and location of plant litter inputs to soils.Therefore, change in land cover are used to estimate changes in carbon stock for mineral soils and default annual emission factors to estimate the losses of carbon following drainage and/or fire for organic soils. Land cover in 2015 is compared to the baseline period (2001-2014) to measure vegetative loss by category and estimate changes in carbon stock.",
"source":"Hengl, T., Mendes de Jesus, J., Heuvelink, G. B.M., Ruiperez Gonzalez, M., Kilibarda, M. et al., 2017. SoilGrids250m: global gridded soil information based on Machine Learning. PLOS One. Available from: http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0169748",
"link":"http://trends.earth"}

{"description":"Soil Organic Carbon (SOC) is used as a proxy to measure carbon stocks responsible for assessing degradation resulting from changes in carbon stocks. Changes in vegetation cover, including those in response to climate or land use or management, influence SOC stocks by altering the rates, quality, and location of plant litter inputs to soils.Therefore, change in land cover are used to estimate changes in carbon stock for mineral soils and default annual emission factors to estimate the losses of carbon following drainage and/or fire for organic soils. Land cover in 2015 is compared to the baseline period to measure vegetative loss by category and estimate changes in carbon stock.",
"source":"<p>Hengl, T., Mendes de Jesus, J., Heuvelink, G. B.M., Ruiperez Gonzalez, M., Kilibarda, M. et al., 2017. SoilGrids250m: global gridded soil information based on Machine Learning. PLOS One. Available from: http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0169748</p><p>ESA Land Cover CCI project team; Defourny, P. (2016): ESA Land Cover Climate Change Initiative (Land_Cover_cci): MERIS Surface Reflectance. Centre for Environmental Data Analysis, 12/15/2017. Available from: http://catalogue.ceda.ac.uk/uuid/e80f28ccb0504c32b403eee654a8a5b3</p><p>UNCCD 2017. Good Practice Guidance. SDG Indicator 15.3.1. Proportion of land that is degraded over total land area. Version 1.0 Available from: http://www2.unccd.int/sites/default/files/relevant-links/2017-10/Good%20Practice%20Guidance_ SDG%20Indicator%2015.3.1_Version%201.0.pdf</p><p>Trends.Earth. Conservation International. Available online at: http://trends.earth. 2018.</p>",
"link":"http://trends.earth"}

